While the state\'92s internal organs were being politicized, its gaze turned outward, sorting people by origin and belief. The State Department halted visitor visas for children from Gaza seeking medical care in the United States after a far-right influencer falsely portrayed them as a security threat. A program that had quietly brought sick children for treatment was frozen in response to online agitation. At the same time, the department announced that it had revoked more than 6,000 student visas since January, claiming\'97without providing evidence\'97that two-thirds were tied to crimes such as assault and burglary or to support for terrorism. It also began a policy of \'93continuous vetting\'94 for all 55 million visa holders, monitoring social media and other data for signs of overstays, criminal activity, or \'93anti-American\'94 views.\
