On the ground, immigration enforcement took on a more secretive and punitive cast. In Monterey County, California, school officials warned that stepped-up Immigration and Customs Enforcement raids were scaring families into keeping children home, threatening attendance and learning, especially for homeless and undocumented students. In Los Angeles, masked agents in unmarked vehicles detained an eighteen-year-old, Benjamin Marcelo Guerrero-Cruz, as he walked his dog, spiriting him away to a detention center in Adelanto. His family described the arrest as a kidnapping. In New Jersey, a warehouse raid saw dozens of workers led away in zip ties, while those with legal status were marked with yellow wristbands. ICE used a Sheraton hotel in Alexandria, Louisiana, to detain a father and son before deporting them to Ecuador, despite Marriott\'92s earlier pledge not to allow its properties to be used for detentions. Another Sheraton in the same city, part of the same chain, was revealed to have hosted migrant families in custody. The line between hotel and holding cell blurred.\
