The administration moved to expand this apparatus. Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem urged ICE to use new funding to buy and operate its own fleet of airplanes, a dedicated deportation airline that former officials said could double monthly removals. ICE planned to spend more than $2.4 million on SUVs and custom vehicle wraps emblazoned with \'93DEFEND THE HOMELAND,\'94 selecting contractors without an open bidding process. The agency launched a social media campaign featuring stylized images of militarized vehicles and a rap soundtrack, recruiting for a vision of immigration enforcement that looked more like a paramilitary operation than a civil agency. The Pentagon, for its part, compiled a list of \'93LA Hotels to Avoid\'94 after protests targeted properties housing ICE and CBP agents, underscoring how deeply immigration enforcement had penetrated civilian spaces. Enforcement and spectacle were now intertwined.\
